('palantir', 'Palantir',
 'AI-powered data fusion and decision intelligence platform for defense and intelligence missions',
 E'Palantir is the dominant AI analytics and data fusion platform for defense, intelligence, and national security applications, with a commercial platform that extends to large enterprise use cases. The company''s two core platforms - Palantir Gotham for defense and intelligence customers, and Palantir Foundry for commercial and government civilian use - share a common architecture built around the ability to integrate heterogeneous data sources, apply AI and machine learning models, and deliver actionable intelligence through operational workflows rather than static dashboards.\n\nFor defense and intelligence customers, Palantir Gotham processes multi-source intelligence data - signals intelligence, imagery, human intelligence, open-source reporting - into a fused operational picture that analysts can query and act on in near-real-time. The platform''s graph-based data model captures entities, relationships, and events across disparate data sources, enabling analysts to connect patterns across datasets that traditional siloed intelligence systems cannot surface. Palantir has deployed mission-critical systems for US Special Operations Command, NATO, and multiple allied defense forces, with operational track records in counterterrorism, logistics, and battlefield coordination.\n\nPalantir''s AI Platform (AIP) released in 2023 brings large language model capabilities into both Gotham and Foundry, enabling natural-language querying of intelligence databases, AI-assisted threat assessment, and automated operational planning support. For defense organizations and government agencies evaluating AI for mission-critical applications where data security, auditability, and operational reliability are non-negotiable requirements, Palantir''s deployment track record across the US and allied defense establishments represents a validation baseline that no other commercial AI platform can match.',
 'https://palantir.com', 'https://palantir.com',
 'paid', false, NULL, 4.5, 2100, false, true, false,
 ARRAY['defense-ai', 'data-analytics', 'government'],
 ARRAY['Mission-proven deployment across US Special Operations Command, NATO, and allied defense forces', 'Multi-source data fusion integrates SIGINT, IMINT, HUMINT, and OSINT into unified operational picture', 'AI Platform (AIP) brings LLM natural language querying into defense and intelligence workflows', 'Graph-based entity relationship model surfaces cross-dataset patterns that siloed systems miss'],
 ARRAY['Government and defense contracts require long procurement cycles and security clearance processes', 'Commercial and civilian deployment requires significant implementation investment and dedicated platform engineers', 'Pricing is enterprise-only - not accessible to smaller defense contractors or startups', 'Platform complexity requires dedicated Palantir Forward Deployed Engineers for full capability deployment'],
 ARRAY['Multi-source intelligence fusion for threat analysis and operational planning in defense missions', 'Logistics and supply chain optimization for large-scale military and government operations', 'AI-assisted decision support for mission planning, targeting, and resource allocation workflows'],
 NOW()),

('anduril', 'Anduril Industries',
 'Autonomous defense systems platform combining AI, robotics, and sensor fusion for national security',
 E'Anduril Industries builds autonomous defense systems from a software-first platform called Lattice - an AI operating system for defense that integrates sensors, drones, autonomous vehicles, and human operators into a unified command-and-control network. Unlike traditional defense contractors that build hardware-centric systems with software as an afterthought, Anduril treats Lattice as the core product and builds hardware specifically designed to be orchestrated by it.\n\nLattice processes data from physical sensors - radar, cameras, acoustic sensors, networked drones - fuses it into a real-time operational picture, and enables human operators to command autonomous systems through a modern software interface rather than specialized military hardware. The system is designed for the US Department of Defense''s vision of multi-domain operations: where ground, air, sea, space, and cyber assets must be coordinated simultaneously at a pace that human commanders cannot maintain without AI assistance. Anduril has deployed systems for US Customs and Border Protection for autonomous border surveillance, US Special Operations Command for persistent surveillance missions, and the Royal Australian Air Force for autonomous combat air vehicle programs.\n\nThe Autonomous Combat Vehicle and Ghost autonomous surveillance drone are hardware products built to run on Lattice, demonstrating the end-to-end system integration that defines Anduril''s approach. For defense procurement teams evaluating next-generation autonomous systems, Anduril represents the most credible challenger to traditional prime contractors on software-defined autonomous capability. The company is not a software platform that customers configure - it delivers integrated hardware-software systems under government contracts.',
 'https://anduril.com', 'https://anduril.com',
 'paid', false, NULL, 4.4, 680, false, true, false,
 ARRAY['defense-ai', 'autonomous-systems', 'robotics'],
 ARRAY['Lattice AI operating system integrates all sensors, drones, and autonomous vehicles into one command network', 'Deployed by USCBP, USSOCOM, and Royal Australian Air Force in operational missions', 'Software-first architecture enables rapid capability updates without hardware replacement cycles', 'Multi-domain operations design supports simultaneous ground, air, and maritime coordination'],
 ARRAY['Products are sold exclusively through US and allied government defense procurement channels', 'Hardware integration timelines require months to years for full operational deployment', 'Lattice platform is proprietary - not available for commercial or civilian application development', 'Export control restrictions apply to all Anduril platforms and technology'],
 ARRAY['Autonomous border and perimeter surveillance with AI-powered threat detection and classification', 'Persistent maritime and coastal surveillance using networked drone and sensor arrays', 'Multi-domain command and control integration for joint force operations requiring real-time situational awareness'],
