('shield-ai', 'Shield AI',
 'AI pilot technology for autonomous flight in GPS-denied and contested environments',
 E'Shield AI builds AI-powered autonomy for military aircraft - enabling unmanned systems to complete missions in environments where GPS is denied, communications are jammed, and traditional autopilot systems fail. The company''s core technology is the Nova AI pilot, a navigation and decision-making system that can fly aircraft autonomously through contested airspace using onboard sensors alone, without external navigation signals or real-time operator communication.\n\nNova has been deployed on multiple unmanned aerial systems for US defense missions, demonstrating autonomous navigation and target prosecution in operationally realistic conditions. The system does not simply follow pre-programmed flight paths - it adapts dynamically to the environment, avoiding obstacles, responding to sensor data, and completing mission objectives in conditions that would ground traditional remotely piloted aircraft. Shield AI acquired Heron Systems in 2021, adding AI-powered dogfighting and air combat maneuver capability - Heron''s AI defeated an F-16 pilot in DARPA''s AlphaDogfight Trials five to zero.\n\nShield AI''s V-BAT unmanned aircraft, operated by the Nova AI pilot, is designed for intelligence, surveillance, and reconnaissance missions requiring vertical takeoff and landing capability without runway infrastructure. For US and allied defense organizations evaluating autonomous flight for missions where GPS vulnerability and communications disruption are operational realities - a growing category as contested environments become the norm - Shield AI represents the most combat-validated AI pilot technology currently in service. The company operates exclusively in the defense sector and does not offer commercial aviation products.',
 'https://shield.ai', 'https://shield.ai',
 'paid', false, NULL, 4.3, 420, false, true, false,
 ARRAY['defense-ai', 'autonomous-systems', 'aerospace'],
 ARRAY['Nova AI pilot enables autonomous flight in GPS-denied and communications-jammed environments', 'Heron Systems AI defeated F-16 pilot five to zero in DARPA AlphaDogfight Trials', 'V-BAT VTOL aircraft provides ISR capability without runway infrastructure requirements', 'Combat-deployed in operational US defense missions requiring denied-environment navigation'],
 ARRAY['Defense-sector only - no commercial or civilian aviation applications', 'Sales exclusively through US and allied government defense procurement and acquisition channels', 'Export controls restrict platform deployment to vetted allied nations', 'Mission system integration requires dedicated Shield AI field deployment teams'],
