('maxar', 'Maxar Technologies',
 'Satellite imagery and geospatial AI analytics platform for defense, intelligence, and commercial use',
 E'Maxar Technologies is the leading provider of high-resolution satellite imagery and AI-powered geospatial analytics for defense, intelligence, and commercial applications. The company operates a constellation of commercial earth observation satellites including WorldView-3 and WorldView Legion, capable of capturing 30-centimeter resolution imagery that enables object detection, change detection, and activity analysis at resolutions that reveal operationally relevant ground truth.\n\nMaxar''s SecureWatch platform provides US government and allied defense customers with on-demand access to the global satellite imagery archive combined with AI-powered analysis tools: automated object detection for vehicles, aircraft, and military equipment, change detection that highlights construction activity or force movements since the last image, and time-series analysis that identifies patterns of activity over extended periods. The Precision3D geospatial data product provides three-dimensional terrain and building models derived from satellite stereo imagery, supporting precision navigation, mission planning, and targeting operations.\n\nFor commercial customers - infrastructure operators, insurance companies, agricultural businesses - Maxar provides Vivid imagery basemaps and AI analytics through its commercial platform. The dual defense-commercial model provides revenue diversity while the commercial data rights fund the satellite constellation capacity that defense customers depend on. Maxar was acquired by Advent International in 2023, providing capital for the WorldView Legion constellation expansion that significantly increases imagery collection capacity and revisit frequency over critical areas. For government and intelligence customers that need the highest-resolution commercial satellite imagery available with AI analysis tools built for operational use, Maxar is the tier-one provider.',
 'https://maxar.com', 'https://maxar.com',
 'paid', false, NULL, 4.4, 890, false, false, false,
 ARRAY['defense-ai', 'satellite-imagery', 'geospatial'],
 ARRAY['WorldView-3 provides 30cm resolution imagery - highest commercially available resolution for object detection', 'SecureWatch platform combines archive imagery with AI object detection and change detection analysis', 'Precision3D terrain and building models support precision navigation and mission planning', 'Global coverage with frequent revisit times over priority areas via WorldView Legion constellation'],
 ARRAY['Government-grade SecureWatch access requires security clearance and contract procurement processes', 'Satellite tasking for specific geographic areas has lead time dependent on constellation availability', 'Commercial pricing for high-resolution archive and collection tasking is significant for sustained operational use', 'AI analysis tools require some geospatial expertise to configure and interpret effectively'],
