('slingshot-aerospace', 'Slingshot Aerospace',
 'Space domain awareness platform using AI to track satellites, debris, and threats in Earth orbit',
 E'Slingshot Aerospace builds space domain awareness technology - the ability to understand what is happening in Earth orbit, which objects are where, and what threats or conjunction risks exist for operational satellites and space assets. As the number of satellites in low Earth orbit has exploded past 10,000 active objects and debris fields have expanded proportionally, the ability to monitor, predict, and respond to space domain events has become a national security imperative and a commercial satellite operations necessity.\n\nThe Slingshot Beacon platform ingests data from ground-based radar and telescope networks, space-based sensors, and commercial tracking sources, applying AI to fuse multi-source observations into the most accurate and current orbital catalog available to non-government customers. The platform provides conjunction analysis - predicting close approaches between tracked objects - and maneuver planning recommendations to minimize collision risk for operational satellites. Slingshot also provides space weather monitoring, tracking solar events that affect satellite operations and radio communications.\n\nFor US Space Force and allied space commands, Slingshot has developed tools for adversarial space activity monitoring - tracking launches, maneuvers, and object behavior that may indicate counter-space operations. The platform''s AI continuously refines orbital predictions as new tracking data arrives, improving the accuracy of conjunction alerts and reducing both false positive maneuver recommendations (which waste fuel) and false negatives (which create collision risk). For commercial satellite operators and defense space program offices that need space domain awareness beyond what government catalog services provide, Slingshot represents a purpose-built AI-native alternative to government-dependent data sources.',
 'https://slingshotaerospace.com', 'https://slingshotaerospace.com',
 'paid', false, NULL, 4.2, 280, false, false, false,
 ARRAY['defense-ai', 'space-tech', 'geospatial'],
 ARRAY['Multi-source data fusion creates more accurate orbital catalog than single-source government data', 'AI conjunction analysis provides actionable maneuver recommendations to minimize satellite collision risk', 'Adversarial space activity monitoring for counter-space threat detection and attribution', 'Space weather integration covers solar events that affect satellite operations and RF communications'],
 ARRAY['Platform access for defense applications requires security clearance review and contract procurement', 'Orbital tracking accuracy depends on sensor network coverage - gaps exist in polar and deep-space regions', 'Maneuver recommendation automation is advisory only - operators retain decision authority', 'Commercial pricing for sustained catalog access requires enterprise subscription'],
 ARRAY['Conjunction analysis and collision avoidance for commercial satellite constellation operations', 'Space domain awareness for US Space Force and allied defense space commands monitoring adversarial activity', 'Space weather monitoring and solar event impact assessment for satellite operations planning'],
