('hawkeye-360', 'HawkEye 360',
 'RF geolocation satellite constellation for signals intelligence and maritime domain awareness',
 E'HawkEye 360 operates a constellation of small satellites equipped with radio frequency (RF) sensors that detect, geolocate, and characterize radio emissions from the Earth''s surface. Unlike optical satellites that require clear skies and daylight, RF sensing works day and night through cloud cover, enabling persistent monitoring of emissions from ships, aircraft, and ground installations that use radio communications or navigation systems. The capability is foundational for maritime domain awareness, illegal activity detection, and signals intelligence at global scale.\n\nThe core application for maritime domain awareness is detecting vessels that have disabled their Automatic Identification System (AIS) transponders - a common tactic used by vessels engaged in illegal fishing, sanctions evasion, drug trafficking, or unauthorized approaches to restricted areas. HawkEye 360''s RF sensors can detect the radio emissions these vessels continue to generate even with AIS disabled, geolocating them with precision sufficient for maritime patrol coordination. The platform has been used to expose North Korean ship-to-ship petroleum transfers in violation of international sanctions, document illegal fishing activity in exclusive economic zones, and identify unregistered vessel activity in contested waters.\n\nFor defense and intelligence customers, the RF sensing capability extends to detecting ground-based radar emissions, monitoring electronic warfare activity, and tracking aircraft that are operating with transponders disabled. HawkEye 360 processes the raw RF detection data through AI analysis pipelines that classify emitter types, correlate observations across time to establish movement patterns, and flag anomalous behavior for analyst review. For government agencies, coast guards, and commercial maritime intelligence services that need persistent global RF monitoring without satellite communication infrastructure requirements, HawkEye 360 provides a unique capability not available from optical imagery providers.',
 'https://he360.com', 'https://he360.com',
 'paid', false, NULL, 4.3, 310, false, false, false,
 ARRAY['defense-ai', 'satellite-imagery', 'geospatial'],
 ARRAY['RF geolocation detects vessels and emitters regardless of weather, cloud cover, or AIS status', 'Proven track record exposing North Korean sanctions violations and illegal fishing operations', 'AI classification pipeline identifies emitter types and anomalous behavior from raw RF detections', 'Day-night persistent global coverage from small satellite constellation at lower cost than optical alternatives'],
 ARRAY['Geolocation precision is lower than optical satellite imagery - suitable for area awareness not precise targeting', 'Satellite revisit frequency limits real-time tracking for fast-moving assets', 'Government intelligence-grade access requires security clearance and NDA-bound procurement', 'Analysis requires RF domain expertise to interpret emitter classification and behavior patterns correctly'],
 ARRAY['Maritime domain awareness and dark vessel detection for coast guard and naval patrol coordination', 'Sanctions enforcement monitoring for ship-to-ship transfers and port calls in restricted waters', 'Electronic order of battle analysis and adversarial radar emission monitoring for defense intelligence programs'],
