('planet-labs', 'Planet Labs',
 'Daily global satellite imagery and AI analytics for continuous Earth monitoring at scale',
 E'Planet Labs operates the largest earth observation satellite constellation in history - over 200 Dove small satellites that image the entire landmass of Earth every single day. Where traditional high-resolution satellites like Maxar''s WorldView provide detailed imagery of specific areas on demand, Planet''s approach trades some resolution (3-5 meters versus 30 centimeters) for complete global coverage and daily revisit - creating a continuous visual record of change on Earth''s surface that enables analysis that single-pass high-resolution systems cannot support.\n\nThe daily cadence is the product''s defining capability. Planet''s Analytic Feed and Planet Basemaps provide pre-processed, analysis-ready imagery that customers can compare day-over-day to detect change without specialist image processing expertise. AI models trained on Planet''s archive detect deforestation, agricultural crop stress, infrastructure construction progress, vessel movements, flood extent, and wildfire perimeter expansion automatically - turning raw imagery into alerts and quantified change metrics. The Planet Fusion product harmonizes Planet imagery with Sentinel-2 and Landsat data to fill cloud cover gaps, improving temporal completeness for time-series applications.\n\nFor defense and intelligence customers, Planet''s daily coverage enables activity-based intelligence at global scale - monitoring training areas, airfields, and port facilities for activity changes that indicate operational preparation. For commercial customers in agriculture, forestry, finance, and supply chain monitoring, the daily cadence enables operational decisions - crop insurance assessment, ESG deforestation compliance monitoring, commodity supply chain tracking - that would be impossible with less frequent imagery. Planet offers commercial API access with tiered pricing models, making satellite imagery accessible to analytics teams that could not previously justify satellite data costs.',
 'https://planet.com', 'https://planet.com',
 'paid', false, NULL, 4.4, 760, false, false, false,
 ARRAY['defense-ai', 'satellite-imagery', 'geospatial'],
 ARRAY['200+ satellite constellation images entire Earth landmass every single day without exception', 'AI analytics pipeline automatically detects deforestation, crop stress, construction, and vessel movement', 'Planet Fusion fills cloud cover gaps using Sentinel-2 and Landsat data for complete time series', 'Commercial API access makes daily satellite imagery accessible to analytics teams at competitive pricing'],
 ARRAY['3-5 meter resolution is lower than Maxar WorldView - not suitable for vehicle or object-level identification', 'Cloud cover reduces optical imagery utility in tropical regions during wet season', 'AI detection models require validation and tuning for specific use cases and geographies', 'Large-area analysis generates significant data volumes requiring cloud compute infrastructure'],
