('helsing', 'Helsing',
 'European defense AI company building software for air, land, and maritime defense missions',
 E'Helsing is a European defense AI company founded in 2021 by former machine learning researchers and defense industry veterans, building AI software for the specific requirements of European defense programs. The company''s focus is on three mission areas: air combat AI for analysis and decision support in fast-moving airborne engagements, ground systems AI for armored vehicle sensor fusion and threat classification, and maritime surveillance AI for submarine and surface threat detection.\n\nHelsingi''s air defense work centers on the Eurofighter Typhoon program, where the company is developing AI systems that process sensor data, identify threats, and recommend tactical responses at speeds that human pilots cannot match in modern air combat. The company is building AI trained on classified operational data - a requirement for defense AI that is genuinely useful in modern contested environments, as opposed to AI trained on open-source or commercial datasets that may not reflect real adversary behavior. Helsing has signed contracts with the German and UK defense ministries, positioning it as the primary European alternative to US-dominted defense AI suppliers.\n\nThe strategic rationale for a European defense AI company is significant: European NATO members face increasing pressure to develop defense technology that does not depend entirely on US suppliers, both for sovereignty reasons and because US export control laws restrict what capabilities European allies can receive. Helsing builds European-sovereign AI for defense applications where data security, national security classification requirements, and political independence from US technology supply chains are requirements. For European defense ministries and prime contractors evaluating AI software suppliers, Helsing represents the emerging alternative to Palantir and US AI defense companies for European program requirements.',
 'https://helsing.ai', 'https://helsing.ai',
