('rebellion-defense', 'Rebellion Defense',
 'AI software platform for DoD decision intelligence, mission planning, and threat analysis',
 E'Rebellion Defense builds AI software specifically for US Department of Defense customers who need AI capabilities that meet government security, classification, and acquisition requirements. The company was founded by defense and intelligence community veterans who recognized that commercial AI tools cannot be deployed in classified mission environments without substantial rearchitecting - and that the US defense community needed a company willing to build AI natively for that environment from the start.\n\nThe company''s core products address mission planning, intelligence analysis, and decision support: Nova Intelligence is an AI-powered system for processing, synthesizing, and querying large volumes of intelligence reporting; Argus provides AI-assisted mission planning for complex operational scenarios; and the Rebellion Platform provides a common AI infrastructure for building additional mission applications in classified environments. All products are designed for air-gapped and classified network deployment, meeting DoD Impact Level requirements that commercial cloud AI cannot satisfy.\n\nRebellion Defense has been selected for multiple DoD and Intelligence Community programs including contracts with US Air Force, US Army, and defense agencies. The company operates with a distributed team that holds active security clearances, enabling rapid deployment to classified customer sites. For DoD program offices evaluating AI software vendors, Rebellion Defense combines the software development culture and talent base of a modern technology company with the security posture, clearance infrastructure, and mission focus that government acquisition requires. The company was acquired by General Dynamics Information Technology (GDIT) in 2024, providing scale and additional contract vehicle access while maintaining the mission-focused product culture.',
