('scale-ai-defense', 'Scale AI Defense',
 'AI data labeling and model evaluation platform purpose-built for US defense and intelligence missions',
 E'Scale AI Defense is the defense and national security division of Scale AI, the leading AI data infrastructure company. While Scale AI''s commercial platform serves autonomous vehicle, robotics, and enterprise AI customers with data labeling and model evaluation services, the Defense division operates under a separate security structure to serve US Department of Defense, Intelligence Community, and allied government customers who require data handling at security classifications that commercial cloud infrastructure cannot support.\n\nThe core capability is building the training data and evaluation infrastructure for AI models used in defense applications: annotating satellite imagery for object detection models, labeling sensor data for autonomous vehicle and drone perception systems, and constructing evaluation benchmarks for AI systems used in intelligence analysis and military decision support. AI models are only as good as the data they are trained on, and the bottleneck for defense AI development is often not algorithmic capability but the availability of properly labeled, security-appropriate training data at the scale required for production-grade models.\n\nScale AI Defense has worked with the US Air Force, DARPA, and the Department of Defense''s Chief Digital and AI Office (CDAO) on programs including Project Maven - the DoD''s flagship AI initiative for applying machine learning to drone footage analysis and intelligence workflows. The company''s Mechanical Turk-style human-in-the-loop labeling infrastructure operates with cleared personnel for classified data programs. For defense AI program offices that have the algorithmic capability to build AI models but face the chronic challenge of acquiring, managing, and labeling training data at the quality and scale required for operational deployment, Scale AI Defense addresses the data infrastructure gap that limits most defense AI programs.',
 'https://scale.com/defense', 'https://scale.com/defense',
 'paid', false, NULL, 4.3, 380, false, false, false,
